\line
## STAR (Dual-Lane)\line
\line
**S — Situation:** one line (context & stakes).  \line
**T — Target (from A.4):** 3–5 criteria (each with **OWNER** + **DATA SOURCE**).  \line
**A — Approach:** methods + system + **design type**; sample frame; constraints; **instruments/logs**.  \line
**R — Results:**  \line
- **Impact:** ROI/adoption/efficiency/risk deltas.  \line
- **Evidence:** observed vs target; **effect sizes**; **CI/SE**; assumption checks; key **ablations**.  \line
**Decision:** **GO / PIVOT / PAUSE** → see **C.3**.\line
\line
---\line
\line
## A — Anchor & Aim\line
- **A.1 Provocation & Problem** — core challenge; stakes.  \line
- **A.2 Prior Art & Theory** — 1–2 key works; how this enters the conversation.  \line
- **A.3 Audience, Assumptions, Constraints** — who; beliefs; hard bounds.  \line
- **A.4 Hypotheses & Success Criteria** — **Each hypothesis → 1 criterion** (OWNER + DATA SOURCE).\line
\line
---\line
\line
## R — Research & Realization\line
- **R.1 Methods & Findings** — how you obtained **3–5** insights.  \line
- **R.2 System Design & Implementation** — hardest problem → alternatives → final.  \line
- **R.3 Iterations & Decision Gates** — visual evolution; include ≥1 **killed** gate.\line
\line
---\line
\line
## C — Characterization, Critique, & Continuation\line
\line
### C.1 Standard / Lite (Quant/Hybrid)\line
```\line
| Criterion (A.4) | Target | Observed | N / CI or SE | Baseline/Control | Ablation / Note | Data Source | Status |\line
|---|---:|---:|---|---:|---|---|---|\line
```\line
*Status:* Pass | Partial | Fail • Include ≥1 ablation and effect size if applicable.\line
\line
### C.1 Qual (Exploratory)\line
```\line
| Criterion (A.4) | Operational Definition | Evidence (n/%/saturation) | Reliability (κ/α) | Excerpts (ID, task, date) | Status |\line
|---|---|---|---|---|---|\line
```\line
*Status:* Supported | Mixed | Not Supported | Emergent • Report IRR & saturation if used.\line
\line
**Observed behavior summary:** one paragraph tying results back to **A.4**.\line
\line
### C.2 Critique (Limits & Validity)\line
Internal / External / Construct / Statistical validity; Reliability; Instrumentation/Drift; Failure modes; Bias/Ethics/Accessibility.\line
\line
### C.3 Continuation (Decision & Plan)\line
**Decision** (GO/PIVOT/PAUSE) • **Plan** (owners, dates) • **Triggers** • **Kill-criteria** • **Risks & mitigations** • **Ethics/Compliance**\line
